cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MA 

The paper proposes a reinforcement learning solution for the real-time bidding problem in sponsored search auctions. This involves handling a complex dynamic environment with stochastic user query behavior and multiple keyword bidding policies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves handling large amounts of data and making decisions in a multi-agent environment, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) respectively.
